<h3><%= I18n.t("questions.FAQ.how_much_does_juvenile_expungement_cost", :default => "How much does juvenile expungement cost?") %></h3>
<p>It costs $124 to expunge a single arrest, plus an extra $64 for each additional arrest. However, many people qualify for a fee waiver that makes expungement free.</p>

<h3><%= I18n.t("questions.FAQ.how_long_does_the_process_take", :default => "How long does the process take?") %></h3>
<p><%= I18n.t("questions.FAQ.usually_a_court_date_is_scheduled_about_15_months_from_the_petition_date_after_a_judge_approves_the_petition_on_the_court_date_it_takes_about_2_months_for_the_police_to_erase_records_so_35_months_total_if_necessary_expungement_can_be_expedited_to_about_25_months_total", :default => "Usually, a court date is scheduled about 1.5 months from the petition date. After a judge approves the petition on the court date, it takes about 2 months for the police to erase records. So, 3.5 months total. If necessary, expungement can be expedited to about 2.5 months total.") %></p>

<h3><%= I18n.t("questions.FAQ.after_i_petition_for_juvenile_expungement_what_are_the_chances_that_my_petition_will_be_approved", :default => "After I petition for juvenile expungement, what are the chances that my petition will be approved?") %></h3>
<p>Whether your petition is approved is up to the judge. However, in the past, <a href="http://chiyouthjustice.wordpress.com/2013/02/04/cook-county-juvenile-expungement-numbers-vs-arrests/"><%= I18n.t("questions.FAQ.almost_all", :default => "almost all") %></a> petitions have been approved.</p>
